This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during a meeting with governors in the East Room. The President thanked the First Lady, the Vice President, and the governors for their work. He mentioned that the states are doing well and offered his assistance to the governors. The President proposed a different format for the meeting, where the press would leave and the governors could ask questions and make statements. He expressed his appreciation for the military, the bands, and the chefs. The President highlighted recent accomplishments, such as trade deals with China, Japan, Mexico, and Canada, and the renegotiation of the deal with South Korea. He congratulated the governors on their records of success and praised their work. The President concluded by thanking the media for attending.